13/07/2003
KOS, Greece -- The 6th annual symposium on transatlantic relations ended Friday (11 July) on the Aegean island of Kos. The event, sponsored by the Andreas Papandreou Foundation, was hosted by Foreign Minister George Papandreou. A total of 42 participants, including former US President Bill Clinton, former US Secretary of State Richard Holbrooke, former Turkish Foreign and Economy Ministers Ismael Cem and Kemal Dervis, and former Portuguese Prime Minister Antonio Guterres, discussed international economic imbalances, the new security agenda, policies concerning culture and religion, and global governance based on democratic institutions. (ANA, MPA - 11/07/03)
